The syntype from Ehrenberg's expedition was collected at El Tor, Sinai, Egypt , in
November 1823
. It is lost, and its subspecific identity remains unknown. However, Pallid Scops Owls are vagrants to the Sinai, with only the two historical specimen records from
1823 and 1891
discussed herein (
Goodman & Meininger 1989 : 323
), and two recent sightings (
Moldovan 2009
). Subspecific identity is unknown for most Sinai records (although exiguus was suggested for the recent sight records;
Moldovan 2009
), but the specimen collected in 1891 belongs to the small southern form (see below).

